WEBVTT

00:02.596 --> 00:20.085
The books that you need is Seymour de Rich's English bookletters, which is fairly out of date now, because it was written in 1930, but it's still the only sort of consecutive coherent one-volume account of English bookletting.

00:20.726 --> 00:27.557
